news.title: Greater Noida development body to conduct survey of STPs in housing societies
news.para: The Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) will check if STPs have been installed in all societies, even the ones that have secured completion certificates recently.

news.title: Gurugram: Sushant Lok RWA goes to DTCP over poor upkeep
news.para: Sushant Lok Extension includes Sushant Lok-2 and 3. In his complaint, RWA secretary R P Mittal said maintenance services in the area are pathetic, be it related to roads, sanitation, security or horticulture.

news.title: Delhi government has so far fined 165 construction sites for violation of dust norms
news.para: Under the Delhi government's anti-dust campaign, so far 522 construction sites have been inspected and fines worth Rs 53.5 lakh have been imposed on 165 of them for the violation of dust mitigation norms.

news.title: Mumbai: SCDRC directs builder to pay compensation to home buyers
news.para: ​The builder was also directed to hand over possession of the 1,070 sq ft flat in Saffire project at Magathane, hand over another flat of the same dimensions in that locality to the complainants or refund the Rs 23 lakh paid for the flat in 2013, along with 18% interest pa.

news.title: Inspire Co-spaces sets up 35,000 sq ft co-working space in Pune's Baner
news.para: It recently acquired a 50,000 sq ft space in Pune’s Kalyani Nagar, with a total capacity of 1,000 seats. Following this expansion in Pune, Inspire co-spaces has a total 6,000 seats across its co-working hubs.

news.title: Aparna Infra Housing buys two office buildings in Hyderabad for Rs 247.5 crore
news.para: The transactions, valued at Rs 247.5 crore, were carried out through Aparna’s subsidiary Hitech CyberSpazio, people aware of the development said.

news.title: ASK Group's offshore fund exits Kumar Properties' Pune project with 1.9 times returns
news.para: The fund has exited from Kumar Properties’ project Kumar Prospera in Pune's Hadapsar locality, which is surrounded by a mix of tech parks, large corporate office buildings, and exclusive gated residential complexes.

news.title: Unitech case: 30 Tihar jail officials suspended
news.para: “Of the 32 personnel, 30 are regular employees, while two are contractual staff (one data entry operator and one nursing orderly),” the DG said.

news.title: H-RERA fines M3M, Suposhaa Realcon & Smart World Developers for 'illegal advertising'
news.para: H-Rera chairman KK Khandelwal said the Authority imposed a penalty of Rs 2.5 crore on M3M Pvt Ltd on Wednesday for advertising boutique floors at its City of Dreams project in Sector 89.

news.title: China's property sector stalked by Evergrande default fears
news.para: Weary Evergrande bondholders still haven't received almost $150 million worth of coupon payments that had been due on Monday, although there was little surprise after the firm had skipped two other payments in recent weeks.

news.title: Shriram Housing Finance gets Rs 300 crore equity capital from parent firm
news.para: ​The company has set a target of crossing Rs 5,600 crore of assets under management (AUM) target by March, as it had already crossed the Rs 4,000-crore mark in July and the new growth capital will help it expand the balance sheet faster.

news.title: China property association to examine difficulties faced by builders: Report
news.para: Tens of thousands of Chinese developers borrowed heavily to build homes during a red-hot property boom between 2016 and 2018, but are now facing a liquidity crunch amid sharply weaker demand and tighter regulations.

news.title: Spain to more than halve subsidy for firms specialised in renting out property
news.para: The discount on the company tax had previously favoured property rental firms over individual landlords - who receive 60% tax rebates for renting out their properties.

news.title: Puravankara to invest Rs 420 crore for two projects
news.para: ​The company on Wednesday launched two projects -- 'Provident Palm Vista' located near Shil Phata, Mumbai with one million square feet of saleable area and 'Tivoli Hills' located near Devanahalli, Bengaluru having a total saleable plot area of about 1.4 million square feet.

news.title: Cement production expected to be up 12% this fiscal: Report
news.para: "Based on the trends so far, ICRA expects the all-India cement production to report an increase by around 12 per cent to 332 million MT in 2021-22, which will be supported by the pent-up demand, rural housing demand and the pick-up in infrastructure activity.
